qas.question: When did many of the ideas that make up western classical music take shape?
What began with the Baroque era?
What era did the classical era follow?
When did the classical era end?
When did the romantic era end?

context: <a0_0><a1_0>The common practice period<a1_0/><a0_0/> is when many of the ideas that make up western classical music took shape, standardized, or were codified. It began with the <a2_0>Baroque era<a2_0/>, running from roughly 1600 to the middle of the 18th century. The Classical era followed, ending roughly <a3_0>around 1820<a3_0/>. The Romantic era ran through the 19th century, ending <a4_0>about 1910<a4_0/>.
